title: USF heads to big road game
text:
USF heads to big road game 
By Dean Pantazi - 21 Alive October 18, 2015 Updated Oct 18, 2015 at 8:44 PM EDT 
FORT WAYNE, Ind. (21Alive) - There will be be no letup for Saint Francis after their 48-7 win over Concordia on Saturday, not with a road trip to ninth ranked 5-1 Robert Morris in Chicago this Saturday. 
The 7-0 seventh ranked Cougars are getting ready in that vein, putting the Concordia win in the rear view mirror and aiming at their quest for a perfect regular season and one or more home playoff games.
